Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:49.82,辉注,,0,0,0,,这里18这个数字是执行实际任务中的数据：\N联盟1号 降落伞故障 1人死亡\N联盟11号 飞船失压 3人死亡\N挑战者号与哥伦比亚号空难 共14人死亡
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,本视频由Brilliant赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,This video is supported by Brilliant.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.98,0:00:08.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,在过去一百年间 航空旅行以其越来越低的票价和越来越高的安全性
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.98,0:00:08.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Over the last 100 years, air travel has become accessible to almost everyone
Dialogue: 1,0:00:08.19,0:00:12.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,已经逐渐深入寻常百姓家
Dialogue: 2,0:00:08.19,0:00:12.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,through the increase in airline safety and the reduction in ticket prices.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.83,0:00:15.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,但飞机再怎么进化
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.83,0:00:15.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,But as current airplanes continue to evolve,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.28,0:00:19.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,物理法则也不会让它再快到哪里去
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.28,0:00:19.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,the limitations of physics have stopped us from going faster and further.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.16,0:00:25.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,但如果有一种能极大缩短飞行时间的旅行方法呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.16,0:00:25.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,But what if there was a new method to Earth travel that would cut flight times massively?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.88,0:00:31.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,航天公司维珍银河和太空叉都在致力于让此事变成现实
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.88,0:00:31.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Space companies Virgin Galactic and SpaceX are trying to make this a reality
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.02,0:00:36.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们想用各自的火箭进行地球上的快速点对点旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.02,0:00:36.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,by using their rocket powered vehicles for super fast travel here on Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.62,0:00:39.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉计划使用他们原本设计用于前往火星的Starship火箭来进行地球旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.62,0:00:39.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX plans to use their Starship rocket,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.20,0:00:44.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉计划使用他们原本设计用于前往火星的Starship火箭来进行地球旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.20,0:00:44.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,primarily designed for Mars, to transport passengers to major cities on Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.77,0:00:48.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些火箭将在地球大气层外飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.77,0:00:48.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since these flights would go above the Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.14,0:00:52.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以火箭的速度会远高于民航客机
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.14,0:00:52.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,it would allow the rocket to reach much higher speeds than an airliner.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.17,0:00:57.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,这意味着地球上任意两点的旅行时间都将小于一小时
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.17,0:00:57.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,This means that flights to anywhere on Earth could be done in less than an hour.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.34,0:01:03.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,飞行应该不会很平稳 因为乘客在起飞着陆的时候回承受几个G的加速度
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.34,0:01:03.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,The ride itself would not be smooth, as passengers would experience g-forces during launch and landing
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.22,0:01:05.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,有点像坐过山车
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.22,0:01:05.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,similar to riding a rollercoaster.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.41,0:01:10.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 旅行中绝大多数时间都是在太空滑行
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.41,0:01:10.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, for the majority of the ride, the rocket would be coasting through space
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.08,0:01:12.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,乘客会感受到失重
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.08,0:01:12.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,and passengers would experience zero-gravity.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.23,0:01:19.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,这让火箭上的厕所和餐车之类常用设施的设计更加复杂
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.23,0:01:19.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,This makes the design of inflight amenities like bathrooms and food carts much more complex.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.58,0:01:25.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 由于飞行时间非常短 这些设施的使用需求应该也不会太高
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.58,0:01:25.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, since the flight times would be so short, the need for such amenities might not be so high.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.05,0:01:30.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,维珍银河也在探寻地球点对点太空旅行的潜力
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.05,0:01:30.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Virgin Galactic is also exploring the potential of Earth to Earth spaceship travel -
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.82,0:01:33.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,但他们的方法完全不同
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.82,0:01:33.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,but their method is completely different.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.64,0:01:38.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们用的不是火箭 而是由火箭驱动的太空飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.64,0:01:38.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead of a rocket, Virgin is developing a rocket powered space-plane
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.19,0:01:42.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,先由飞机带到高空 然后在空中进行发射
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.19,0:01:42.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,which can be carried up to high altitudes and launched in mid-air.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.89,0:01:47.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,两种方法理论上都能极大缩短飞行时间
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.89,0:01:47.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Both methods could theoretically reduce flight times by an enormous margin -
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.32,0:01:51.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在两家公司可以发射乘客到太空之前
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.32,0:01:51.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,but before either of these companies can launch passengers around the globe,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.52,0:01:54.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们要解决一大堆问题
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.52,0:01:54.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,they have to overcome a lot of challenges.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.89,0:01:59.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉为了解决火箭发射时发生的巨大噪音
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.89,0:01:59.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order for SpaceX to get around the enormous amount of sound produced by their rocket,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:59.85,0:02:05.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,发射需要远离城市 很可能是在海中
Dialogue: 2,0:01:59.85,0:02:05.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,launches would need to take place far away from cities, perhaps out in the ocean.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.42,0:02:10.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此需要额外的将乘客运输到发射场的步骤
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.42,0:02:10.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of this will require more transportation for passengers getting to and from the launch site.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.32,0:02:14.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,维珍银河可能这方面的问题比较小
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.32,0:02:14.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,Virgin would likely have less trouble getting regulatory approval
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.50,0:02:19.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为他们的飞机起飞和着陆和普通民航飞机起降没什么区别
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.50,0:02:19.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,since their take off and landing procedure is much more similar to traditional air travel
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.47,0:02:22.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且可以使用目前已有的机场设施
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.47,0:02:22.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,and could use the pre-existing infrastructure of airports.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.32,0:02:27.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,维珍银河计划在全球建立一套太空运输网络
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.32,0:02:27.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,Virgin has plans to build a network of spaceports around the world
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.49,0:02:31.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括当前在英国南部正在开发的一块场地
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.49,0:02:31.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,including one in the south of England which is currently under development.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.71,0:02:36.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,这块额外的太空港可以让维珍银河进行跨大西洋飞行测试
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.71,0:02:36.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,This additional spaceport would allow Virgin to perform transatlantic test flights
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.64,0:02:40.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,测试中他们将往返他们在新墨西哥州已有的太空港
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.64,0:02:40.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,to and from their existing spaceport in New Mexico.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.83,0:02:44.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,但即使两家公司都获取了营业执照
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.83,0:02:44.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,But even if both companies get passed the regulatory approval,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.52,0:02:49.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们在票价上还要面临巨大挑战
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.52,0:02:49.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,they still face massive challenges in the form of ticket prices.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.34,0:02:55.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,火箭需要像民航客机那样可重复使用才能有与其接近的票价
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.34,0:02:55.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,A rocket needs to be as reusable as an airliner in order to achieve similar ticket prices.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.80,0:03:00.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然维珍银河的方案更接近目前的民航旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.80,0:03:00.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although Virgin's plan seems more familiar to current air travel,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.12,0:03:04.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,但想要让票价降到合适的范围内还有很长的路要走
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.12,0:03:04.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,it will have a harder time achieving a reasonable ticket price.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.44,0:03:09.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们的飞机太小 一次只能承载六名旅客和两名飞行员
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.44,0:03:09.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,With such a small vehicle, only 6 passengers and 2 pilots can fly at a time,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.70,0:03:12.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,使得单座价格很高
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.70,0:03:12.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,making the cost per ticket much higher.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.82,0:03:17.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管现在贵的离谱 但还有700多个有意愿的乘客在排队
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.82,0:03:17.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Despite the price, almost 700 eager passengers are already on the waiting list
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.97,0:03:21.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,想要搭乘他们的二号船VSS Unity进行亚轨道飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.97,0:03:21.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,for a suborbital flight aboard VSS Unity.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.86,0:03:25.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在这些载客旅行成为现实之前
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.86,0:03:25.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,But before these passenger flights can become a reality,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.41,0:03:31.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,两家公司还要解决太空飞行的一个最大挑战：安全
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.41,0:03:31.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,both companies will need to overcome one of spaceflight's greatest challenges, safety.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.96,0:03:38.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,在2017年 民航平均每运输六千万人只有一次死亡
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.96,0:03:38.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 2017, the aviation industry had just 1 death for every 60 million passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.57,0:03:44.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,而目前为止 在航天界 这个数字是每32个宇航员死亡一人
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.57,0:03:44.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,So far, the spaceflight industry has a rate of 1 death for every 32 astronauts,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.68,0:03:49.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,总共570人进入太空 其中有18人遇难
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.68,0:03:49.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,since out of the 570 people that have been into space, 18 have died.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.14,0:03:54.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,整个商业航天界想要达到安全的标准还有很长的路要走
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.14,0:03:54.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,Meeting the safety standards remains a challenge across all commercial spaceflight,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.02,0:04:00.45,辉注,,0,0,0,,相关视频：av21807258
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.02,0:04:00.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,尤其在2014年维珍银河的VSS企业号飞机悲剧性的坠毁事故之后
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.02,0:04:00.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,especially after the tragic crash of Virgin's VSS Enterprise in 2014.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:00.96,0:04:04.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,另外 虽然乘客在这样的旅行中可以节省很多时间
Dialogue: 2,0:04:00.96,0:04:04.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although passenger travel could save us a huge amount of time,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.60,0:04:09.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,但大家经常忽视的一个生理上的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.60,0:04:09.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,one thing that is often overlooked is the physiological impacts it could have.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.60,0:04:14.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,以如此快的速度进行环球旅行可能会对身体带来一些奇怪影响
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.60,0:04:14.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,Travelling around the world this fast could have weird effects on our bodies
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.01,0:04:18.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为我们日常黑白轮转的生物钟可能会受到影响
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.01,0:04:18.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,since we would be deprived of the usual day/night cycle.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.56,0:04:21.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,乘客可能看着日出醒来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.56,0:04:21.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Passengers could wake up to watch the sunrise,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.15,0:04:25.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后横穿半个地球 在不到一个小时的时间里看到太阳落山
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.15,0:04:25.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,then travel across the world to watch the sunset in less than an hour.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.98,0:04:30.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,如此快的倒时差可能会带来比常规民航旅行更严重的生理反应
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.98,0:04:30.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,This rapid change in time zones would create a much more intense feeling of jet lag
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.78,0:04:34.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,如此快的倒时差可能会带来比常规民航旅行更严重的生理反应
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.78,0:04:34.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,than we are used to from regular airline travel.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.40,0:04:42.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉和维珍银河能否将太空旅行变为现实目前还是个未知数
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.40,0:04:42.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Whether SpaceX or Virgin Galactic can turn the dream of Earth to Earth rocket travel into a reality remains unknown.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.37,0:04:46.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,但商业航天正朝着实现这种革命性的旅行方式而大步前进
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.37,0:04:46.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, commercial space programs are making huge strides
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.22,0:04:49.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,但商业航天正朝着实现这种革命性的旅行方式而大步前进
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.22,0:04:49.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,towards achieving this revolutionary method of transportation
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.34,0:04:52.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,而我们的前途也是一片光明 令人兴奋！
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.34,0:04:52.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to make our future much more exciting!
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了实现这一雄心勃勃的目标
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to achieve this ambitious goal,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.76,0:05:03.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,两家公司都需要雇佣像你一样对太空感兴趣的 充满激情的人
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.76,0:05:03.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,both of these companies will need to hire people like you that are interested and passionate about all things space.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.33,0:05:08.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后就是猝不及防的恰饭 就不翻了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.33,0:05:08.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if you don't have a formal science education, you can start your learning adventure using Brilliant.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.86,0:05:12.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,Brilliant is a website that makes learning accessible and fun.
